  <p>Recognized as one of the most beautiful villages in France, Saint-Paul de Vence will charm you with its unique atmosphere.</p>
  <p>Fortified medieval village, Saint-Paul de Vence is perched on a rocky outcrop and overlooks the Mediterranean Sea. The calm of its alleys and the exceptional light have always attracted and inspired artists from all over the world.</p>
  <p>You enter this picturesque pedestrian village by crossing the gate in the ramparts. Stroll through the streets and discover small squares, fountains, art craft workshops… Beside the church, the very famous Folon Chapel, decorated by the Belgian artist will seduce you by its calm and serenity.</p>
  <p>The main street is full of galleries featuring all forms of art. A tour of the village along the ramparts will offer you a view of the Mediterranean Sea and the mountains.</p>
  <p>Don't forget to visit the world-famous Maeght Foundation dedicated to modern and contemporary art.</p>
